    <note>Song(2) Shi [8121] His ancestors were Guangping jun Song(2). They subsequently moved to Daming Fu, Guantao xian and then to Jingzhao, Changan xian where Shi was buried. The family of his brother Bi's [3800] grandson, Dao [3803], moved to Henan where Dao died in his private home in Luoyang in 1083, but he was buried in Zhengzhou, Guancheng xian. Dao was Co-intendant of exchange for the San-men rapids in 1071. Dao's elder brother, Di [3804], was dismissed as Hunan yunpan in 1064, subsequently served as Guangxi yunpan, and was placed in charge of implementing the Shenxi exchange medium (jiaozi) laws in 1074. Dao's sons have the same generational name as Ziyong [1582]. Shi was the father-in-law of Yang(2) Xuan's [2005] brother, Yang(2) Tan [4053], and of Wang(2) Zong [1093]. He was Hang's [1563] elder cousin and Xuan's [1566] cousin. Song(2) Zifang [3806], the son-in-law of Wang(2) Shu(1)'s [1877] grandson, Wang(2) Shenyan [3977], was Di's nephew. Fan Chunren, WJ, 13.4a; XCB, 221.25b, 26a (n.), 256.9b; Guangxi TZ, 21.15b; SHY:ZG, 63.23b-24a; Yang Yi, WJ, 8.1a-8b. CBD, 1, 746.</note>
